IMPLEMENTATION PATTERNS
- Parse once: parsed = parseCron(expr); then call nextRun(parsed, after) repeatedly.
- Use deterministic roll-forward algorithm that resets lower-significance fields when a higher-significance field is advanced.
- For timezone-aware computation: convert 'after' to the timezone-local components, perform roll-forward on local fields, then convert back to absolute epoch ms for Date return.

TROUBLESHOOTING
- If nextRun never returns: check maxYears; increase or verify expression is satisfiable.
- If DST results in missing run: confirm timezone option was provided and clarify semantics (UTC vs local).
- If parsing fails on named months or weekdays: ensure names are case-insensitive and normalized before lookup.

